question.title: What will be the target Selic rate (in percent) established by Copom at its March 2026 meeting?
question.description:
This question tracks the exact numerical value of the target Selic rate decided during the March 2026 Copom meeting. The Selic rate is the primary monetary policy tool of the Central Bank of Brazil, used to control inflation and influence economic activity.

`{"format":"bot_tournament_question","info":{"hash_id":"369b5c1c72835c28"}}`
question.resolution_criteria: This question resolves to the exact numerical value of the target Selic rate (taxa Selic) as established by the Central Bank of Brazil's Monetary Policy Committee (Copom) during its scheduled meeting in March 2026. Resolution will be based on information presented by [TradingEconomics](https://tradingeconomics.com/brazil/interest-rate) and/or the official data published by the [Banco Central do Brasil (BCB)](https://www.bcb.gov.br/en/monetarypolicy/selicrate). The value should be expressed as an annualized percentage rate (e.g., 15.0 percent for January 2026).
question.fine_print: The resolution value is the target rate set at the conclusion of the March 2026 meeting. If the March 2026 meeting is cancelled, rescheduled to a date after 2026-05-01, or if no target rate is announced, the question will be resolved as 'Annulled'. In the event of a discrepancy between the English and Portuguese versions of the BCB website, the Portuguese version (bcb.gov.br) shall take precedence. Source: https://www.bcb.gov.br/en/monetarypolicy/copom
